description.narrative: Children and adolescents, families, communities and organizations of prioritized municipalities show favorable changes in their beliefs, level of knowledge, attitudes and diminish practices of violence against children based on a combination of communication tools, channels and approaches that facilitate changes positive social and behavioral, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change, Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change (Covid), Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2021, UNICEF will have contributed to ensuring that children, adolescents and families more disadvantages from the country's priority municipalities have access to improved programmes and services for the care of victims of violence, including gender-based violence, promoting a culture of peace and good treatment, and the timely registration.

description.narrative: VCO increased the knowledge of caregivers, communities and services providers on lifesavings and protective practices related to Child Protection and Gender-based violence. C4D worked with the objective of changing the behavior of families and influencing social norms during the COVID-19 emergency context and to increase and strengthen child protection.C4D supported the construction and dissemination of key messages on psychosocial support, stigmatization prevention because of COVID-19 and promoting good treatment with interventions in social media, SMS, phone calls, printed and audiovisual materials.
